Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1 can} in a #colander{}. Pop half of them into a #bowl{} and crush with the back of a #fork{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Add half the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add half the garlic, the @harissa paste{50%g} and @tomato puree{30g} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Add the @water{as needed} with half the @vegetable stock powder{1/2%tsp} and half the @honey{7.5%g}. Stir well to dissolve the stock powder.

Add the whole and crushed mixed beans to the mixture, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and bring to a simmer. Reduce the heat to medium and simmer until thickened slightly, ~{12-15%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it starts to look dry.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium high heat. Add the remaining onion and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour the @water{as needed} for the @couscous{120%g} into the saucepan with the remaining @vegetable stock powder{1/2%tsp} and bring to the boil. When boiling, remove from the heat and stir in the couscous, pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Pop the @cod fillets{2} into a bowl with a drizzle of @oil{}, the remaining @honey{7.5%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix to coat. Heat a frying pan on high heat and cook until golden brown, ~{2%minutes} each side. Pop the cod onto the mixed bean stew, cover with a lid (or some #foil{}) and cook until the fish is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Stir half the coriander through the couscous. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if you like. Divide the couscous between plates and spoon over the harissa mixed beans and cod. Top with the remaining coriander. Enjoy!